1
00:00:23,273 --> 00:00:25,275
(Arthur Aron's 36 Questions Experiment)

2
00:00:32,323 --> 00:00:33,158
Hello.

3
00:00:33,645 --> 00:00:35,146
You're Jung-yeon, right?

4
00:00:35,171 --> 00:00:36,464
Hello.

5
00:00:36,567 --> 00:00:37,203
Come in.

6
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:37,829
Yes.

7
00:00:42,083 --> 00:00:46,212
(Center for Cognitive
and Emotional Pattern Analysis)

8
00:00:46,744 --> 00:00:49,558
If you come in this way,
this is our office.

9
00:00:55,644 --> 00:00:56,603
Teacher…

10
00:00:56,628 --> 00:00:57,546
Yes?

11
00:01:35,284 --> 00:01:38,480
But why are you calling him "teacher"?

12
00:01:40,172 --> 00:01:43,503
Oh, he was my private tutor in high school.

13
00:01:44,382 --> 00:01:45,464
Ah.

14
00:01:45,609 --> 00:01:47,675
Ha Yu-geon did graduate top
of his department.

15
00:01:50,276 --> 00:01:52,613
But was he like this back then too?

16
00:01:53,011 --> 00:01:54,470
Like what?

17
00:01:54,495 --> 00:01:55,747
I mean…

18
00:01:58,524 --> 00:01:59,817
Was he kind of a jerk?

19
00:02:14,717 --> 00:02:18,888
(7 Years Earlier)

20
00:02:18,888 --> 00:02:19,806
You've been well, right?

21
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:20,974
Yes.

22
00:02:31,458 --> 00:02:32,667
Sigh.

23
00:02:34,793 --> 00:02:35,613
Say hello.

24
00:02:36,072 --> 00:02:37,574
Professor Park's student.

25
00:02:37,913 --> 00:02:39,722
He'll be staying here a few months,

26
00:02:39,747 --> 00:02:42,917
and he goes to Hanguk University
on a scholarship,

27
00:02:42,942 --> 00:02:45,238
so ask him about studying or…

28
00:02:49,207 --> 00:02:51,941
No, forget it.

29
00:02:55,472 --> 00:02:57,043
Ugh, this little—

30
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:06,949
My son, Min Jung-yeon.

31
00:03:08,406 --> 00:03:11,261
He takes after his dad—no manners at all.

32
00:03:13,234 --> 00:03:14,418
Want some coffee?

33
00:03:28,356 --> 00:03:30,399
Like you saw in the email I sent,

34
00:03:30,424 --> 00:03:34,761
the headquarter is developing a dating app,
and we're gathering the data it needs.

35
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:37,383
When you have someone you like,

36
00:03:37,383 --> 00:03:42,305
we'll use VR, cameras,
and biosensors to capture

37
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:44,011
and analyze your facial expressions
and behavior patterns.

38
00:03:45,761 --> 00:03:47,418
Ah… yes.

39
00:03:48,425 --> 00:03:49,722
Jung-yeon,

40
00:03:49,854 --> 00:03:51,814
you'll convert the collected data
into numbers

41
00:03:51,814 --> 00:03:53,399
and archive it.

42
00:03:54,421 --> 00:03:55,755
As you know,

43
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:58,644
it's hard to find test subjects,

44
00:03:59,224 --> 00:04:01,226
so you'll need to participate in
the experiments too.

45
00:04:01,496 --> 00:04:06,144
Hey now—aren't you being a bit cold
to your old student?

46
00:04:10,929 --> 00:04:12,980
Man, he never lets that attitude slide.

47
00:04:13,573 --> 00:04:15,992
Hey, I'm heading to HQ,
then I'm going straight home, okay?

48
00:04:17,621 --> 00:04:18,664
See you, Jung-yeon.

49
00:04:18,689 --> 00:04:20,149
Yes, see you.

50
00:04:48,204 --> 00:04:49,386
Researcher…

51
00:04:49,637 --> 00:04:51,764
I finished everything you asked earlier.

52
00:04:52,962 --> 00:04:53,754
Yeah.

53
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:57,433
Thanks, Jung-yeon.

54
00:05:03,803 --> 00:05:05,144
Teacher…

55
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:07,300
I missed you.

56
00:05:09,029 --> 00:05:10,120
Me too.

57
00:05:16,370 --> 00:05:18,175
You've grown up nicely—pretty, huh?

58
00:05:29,568 --> 00:05:32,972
I don't even know why he's like that.

59
00:05:33,762 --> 00:05:37,082
He used to study a bit in middle school.

60
00:05:39,922 --> 00:05:41,214
Could it be…

61
00:05:41,758 --> 00:05:44,527
that he fell in with a bad crowd?

62
00:05:46,637 --> 00:05:49,074
You think he got corrupted by bad friends?

63
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:52,566
What bad friends?

64
00:05:52,891 --> 00:05:55,811
If he's doing bad things, he's the bad one.

65
00:05:59,525 --> 00:06:01,160
Ever since he started

66
00:06:01,624 --> 00:06:06,894
living separately from his dad,
he's been like that… maybe.

67
00:06:12,665 --> 00:06:14,089
If it's okay with you…

68
00:06:15,304 --> 00:06:19,168
would you mind if I tutored Jung-yeon?

69
00:06:19,326 --> 00:06:24,456
Oh my—really? That would be wonderful.

70
00:06:27,425 --> 00:06:32,941
But if he won't listen,
don't push yourself too hard.

71
00:06:35,277 --> 00:06:37,089
I'll try to talk to him.

72
00:06:38,437 --> 00:06:39,574
Will you?

73
00:06:39,870 --> 00:06:41,699
I'd really appreciate it.

74
00:06:59,976 --> 00:07:01,105
What is it?

75
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:09,691
I'm here to tutor you.

76
00:07:13,555 --> 00:07:18,089
Yeah, go work hard by yourself.

77
00:08:40,686 --> 00:08:41,988
You got hurt again?

78
00:08:54,275 --> 00:08:55,371
Hey.

79
00:08:57,703 --> 00:09:00,332
I'll tell Mom
I'm getting tutoring just fine,

80
00:09:01,495 --> 00:09:04,121
so just take your money
and mind your own business.

81
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:05,562
Huh?

82
00:09:25,111 --> 00:09:26,261
Jung-yeon,

83
00:09:27,298 --> 00:09:29,003
I want to help you.

84
00:09:33,155 --> 00:09:36,332
Worry about your perfect little life.

85
00:09:39,453 --> 00:09:40,496
Is someone bullying you?

86
00:09:40,496 --> 00:09:41,652
Ah shit.

87
00:09:41,812 --> 00:09:43,097
You're crossing a line.

88
00:09:45,126 --> 00:09:46,785
Go study.

89
00:09:47,209 --> 00:09:48,308
Or what,

90
00:09:48,671 --> 00:09:50,918
go flirt with girls with that pretty face.

91
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:06,527
Shi..

92
00:10:08,316 --> 00:10:09,150
Hey.

93
00:10:14,451 --> 00:10:15,661
You wanna die?

94
00:10:24,554 --> 00:10:26,847
I'm going to ask you a few questions now.

95
00:10:27,066 --> 00:10:31,433
Just put on the VR headset
in front of you and answer comfortably.

96
00:11:00,724 --> 00:11:01,850
Whoa.

97
00:11:03,209 --> 00:11:05,128
You see the test app on the screen?

98
00:11:05,998 --> 00:11:07,503
Can you tap that and go in?

99
00:11:08,659 --> 00:11:10,168
Yeah, I'm in.

100
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:14,757
I'll be recording your eye movements
and facial expressions.

101
00:11:15,390 --> 00:11:16,182
Huh?

102
00:11:17,082 --> 00:11:18,875
I can't see anything now.

103
00:11:19,804 --> 00:11:21,222
Then let's begin.

104
00:11:23,391 --> 00:11:24,355
Okay.

105
00:11:26,639 --> 00:11:29,975
Test subject, Case-Delphi,
starting questionnaire.

106
00:11:30,022 --> 00:11:32,983
This experiment is to measure
emotional responses.

107
00:11:32,983 --> 00:11:34,941
All answers will be recorded
via the VR device.

108
00:11:35,444 --> 00:11:37,697
A variety of questions will be presented.

109
00:11:37,697 --> 00:11:40,003
Please let me know
if you feel uncomfortable at any point.

110
00:11:40,094 --> 00:11:41,378
Got it.

111
00:11:42,819 --> 00:11:44,654
How are you feeling right now?

112
00:11:45,340 --> 00:11:47,050
A little nervous.

113
00:11:48,128 --> 00:11:50,172
Alright, we'll proceed.

114
00:11:50,707 --> 00:11:52,542
Are you currently seeing anyone?

115
00:11:52,683 --> 00:11:53,768
No.

116
00:11:54,296 --> 00:11:55,172
Hmm…

117
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:57,824
Then is there someone you like?

118
00:11:59,950 --> 00:12:01,118
Yes.

119
00:12:05,336 --> 00:12:09,902
Can you name three things you have
in common with that person?

120
00:12:11,217 --> 00:12:12,558
Uh…

121
00:12:13,672 --> 00:12:14,980
Good at studying.

122
00:12:15,489 --> 00:12:16,832
Kind.

123
00:12:17,909 --> 00:12:20,495
And if you really get to know them…
kind of scary?

124
00:12:24,222 --> 00:12:25,582
Those are common traits, right?

125
00:12:26,470 --> 00:12:28,363
Yes, they are.

126
00:12:29,344 --> 00:12:32,613
What are you most grateful for
in your life?

127
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:35,261
I…

128
00:12:36,172 --> 00:12:38,574
I used to be really off track.

129
00:12:39,506 --> 00:12:42,675
I didn't listen to my parents,
gave up on studying…

130
00:12:44,513 --> 00:12:45,473
But…

131
00:12:45,977 --> 00:12:47,878
someone held onto me back then.

132
00:12:48,956 --> 00:12:51,441
Even when I was hopeless,
they didn't let go.

133
00:12:58,175 --> 00:13:00,652
If you could change one thing
about your childhood,

134
00:13:02,643 --> 00:13:04,425
what would it be?

135
00:13:13,746 --> 00:13:17,714
I wish I hadn't confessed to
that person so recklessly.

136
00:13:32,232 --> 00:13:33,292
Hyung—

137
00:13:33,466 --> 00:13:34,964
I mean… teacher—

138
00:13:35,979 --> 00:13:38,652
Do you have a girlfriend?

139
00:13:39,944 --> 00:13:41,746
Focus on studying.

140
00:13:43,547 --> 00:13:45,464
If you tell me, I will.

141
00:13:48,569 --> 00:13:49,987
What do you think?

142
00:13:51,872 --> 00:13:52,949
Probably yes.

143
00:13:53,679 --> 00:13:57,105
You go to a good school,
you're tall, handsome…

144
00:13:57,833 --> 00:13:59,285
No, I don't.

145
00:13:59,950 --> 00:14:01,574
Do you like someone?

146
00:14:03,980 --> 00:14:05,190
Uh…

147
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:07,628
I think so.

148
00:14:09,028 --> 00:14:12,035
What do you mean “think so”?
You're not sure?

149
00:14:15,606 --> 00:14:18,160
You're pretty, everyone probably likes you.

150
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:33,285
If you had a chance

151
00:14:33,448 --> 00:14:36,918
to have dinner with just one person
in the world,

152
00:14:40,212 --> 00:14:41,824
who would you choose?

153
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:56,793
Do you want to have dinner with me today?

154
00:14:59,398 --> 00:15:00,519
What should I do?

155
00:15:00,774 --> 00:15:02,472
I have things to do at home tonight.

156
00:15:05,237 --> 00:15:06,238
Ah…

157
00:15:08,490 --> 00:15:10,576
I retook the exam because of you.

158
00:15:12,048 --> 00:15:14,342
Why are you bringing that up now?

159
00:15:14,997 --> 00:15:16,040
And—

160
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:18,003
You chose to retake it.

161
00:15:25,419 --> 00:15:26,293
Then…

162
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,218
Do you want to eat at my place?

163
00:15:37,563 --> 00:15:38,480
Let's go, hurry.

164
00:15:38,520 --> 00:15:39,396
Huh?

165
00:15:39,396 --> 00:15:41,503
Wait, I need to tidy this up.

166
00:15:41,774 --> 00:15:43,519
Ah, I'll do it tomorrow.

167
00:15:43,984 --> 00:15:45,110
Let's go.

168
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:48,906
Come on, hurry.

169
00:15:48,906 --> 00:15:50,449
I need to finish this.

170
00:15:50,449 --> 00:15:53,363
You said you'd buy me dinner, come on.

171
00:16:18,766 --> 00:16:20,847
You remember the day I confessed before?

172
00:16:24,965 --> 00:16:26,308
Do you remember?

173
00:16:28,839 --> 00:16:30,621
You were cute back then.

174
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:35,160
I was pretty young.

175
00:16:36,958 --> 00:16:38,449
You're still cute.

176
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:41,933
Do I still look like a kid to you?

177
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:48,507
Hmm…

178
00:16:53,762 --> 00:16:55,636
You still feel like a high schooler.

179
00:17:31,247 --> 00:17:32,582
Do you still like me?

180
00:17:40,053 --> 00:17:43,910
Back then, you were emotionally unstable,

181
00:17:45,383 --> 00:17:48,449
and I was older than you,
so I probably seemed impressive.

182
00:17:50,444 --> 00:17:52,230
First love at that age

183
00:17:53,251 --> 00:17:55,496
tends to get romanticized as time passes.

184
00:17:59,286 --> 00:18:00,589
So—

185
00:18:02,169 --> 00:18:03,337
Yeah?

186
00:18:04,666 --> 00:18:05,824
So what?

187
00:18:06,527 --> 00:18:08,529
We've only had a few glasses of wine,

188
00:18:09,623 --> 00:18:11,652
and just because I idealized things from
when I was young,

189
00:18:11,847 --> 00:18:14,035
kissing a grown adult man

190
00:18:14,811 --> 00:18:16,402
is supposed to be normal?

191
00:18:19,389 --> 00:18:20,535
That's not what I meant.

192
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:26,386
I'll decide my feelings myself, teacher.

193
00:18:32,910 --> 00:18:34,457
Think about it.

194
00:19:03,365 --> 00:19:05,200
I like you, teacher.

195
00:19:06,804 --> 00:19:08,269
You did well on this.

196
00:19:12,927 --> 00:19:14,303
Please grant me one wish.

197
00:19:15,466 --> 00:19:16,785
A wish?

198
00:19:17,734 --> 00:19:19,569
Did we ever make that kind of promise?

199
00:19:21,811 --> 00:19:23,646
Am I not pretty?

200
00:19:26,563 --> 00:19:28,066
What should I do...

201
00:19:28,854 --> 00:19:30,863
I like smart people.

202
00:19:32,464 --> 00:19:35,019
With these grades,
you wouldn't even get near our school.

203
00:19:46,443 --> 00:19:47,569
Ah.

204
00:19:48,426 --> 00:19:50,553
I really like you, teacher.

205
00:19:50,578 --> 00:19:51,714
You even show up

206
00:19:52,269 --> 00:19:53,687
in my dreams.

207
00:19:59,615 --> 00:20:00,839
Geez.

208
00:20:01,707 --> 00:20:03,035
You're such a kid.

209
00:20:17,916 --> 00:20:19,250
Why isn't Jung-yeon here?

210
00:20:29,436 --> 00:20:30,808
Is he sick or something?

211
00:20:43,617 --> 00:20:44,941
Sorry I'm late.

212
00:20:48,325 --> 00:20:50,886
Whoa—did you get into a fight?

213
00:20:51,173 --> 00:20:53,652
Do you need a lawyer? I know someone.

214
00:20:53,677 --> 00:20:56,871
No, it's nothing. I'm fine.

215
00:20:58,697 --> 00:21:00,285
If it's nothing serious,

216
00:21:00,615 --> 00:21:03,144
let's start the experiment for HQ first.

217
00:21:03,535 --> 00:21:06,037
Wow, that's cold.

218
00:21:06,062 --> 00:21:07,689
Are you insane about work?

219
00:21:07,714 --> 00:21:08,496
Hey.

220
00:21:08,696 --> 00:21:10,441
Do you get paid more than me?

221
00:21:10,686 --> 00:21:12,020
What are you talking about?

222
00:21:16,269 --> 00:21:17,589
Jung-yeon.

223
00:21:19,186 --> 00:21:20,479
Come over here.

224
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:49,199
I'll skip the explanation.

225
00:22:49,534 --> 00:22:52,277
This is Case Delphi, trial six.

226
00:22:53,192 --> 00:22:56,136
What's the most precious memory
of your life?

227
00:22:57,918 --> 00:22:58,917
Um...

228
00:22:59,351 --> 00:23:02,058
I used to spend a lot of time
with my first love.

229
00:23:02,747 --> 00:23:06,441
Every single day back then
was precious to me.

230
00:23:08,063 --> 00:23:10,034
And the worst memory?

231
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:14,675
I confessed, we even kissed.

232
00:23:16,269 --> 00:23:19,183
And then he patted my head

233
00:23:20,354 --> 00:23:23,316
and said it was “just a momentary feeling.”

234
00:23:23,341 --> 00:23:25,574
Wow. What a jerk.

235
00:23:26,063 --> 00:23:28,605
Right? Pretty awful.

236
00:23:30,429 --> 00:23:31,722
Jung-yeon.

237
00:23:34,928 --> 00:23:36,417
Shall we step outside and talk?

238
00:24:03,459 --> 00:24:05,792
Are you rebelling again, now of all times?

239
00:24:09,543 --> 00:24:11,425
Oh, this?

240
00:24:16,689 --> 00:24:19,769
I thought you might care
if I looked beaten up. Like before.

241
00:24:24,853 --> 00:24:26,300
Then what about your hand?

242
00:24:37,009 --> 00:24:38,488
You're still a kid.

243
00:24:41,211 --> 00:24:43,183
I'm grown up now, you know?

244
00:24:44,126 --> 00:24:46,808
You don't need to feel guilty anymore.

245
00:24:47,899 --> 00:24:50,485
If you want to sleep with me, you can.

246
00:24:51,432 --> 00:24:53,517
You've got some nerve for someone so small.

247
00:24:58,946 --> 00:25:00,659
You're not my type.

248
00:25:02,003 --> 00:25:03,792
Yeah, right.

249
00:25:07,576 --> 00:25:09,286
Why do you think that?

250
00:25:10,716 --> 00:25:13,050
You like pretty types like me.

251
00:25:15,630 --> 00:25:17,006
I saw everything.

252
00:25:20,698 --> 00:25:21,991
Saw what?

253
00:25:24,548 --> 00:25:28,495
My observation notes when I was in high school.

254
00:25:58,979 --> 00:26:03,066
(Emotional Attachment Formation and Correction
Experiment in At-Risk Adolescents)

255
00:26:31,131 --> 00:26:34,558
(It was all written there. About me.)

256
00:26:35,870 --> 00:26:38,644
(He shows a strong interest in appearance.)

257
00:26:39,389 --> 00:26:42,730
(Especially when called “pretty,”
he blushes.)

258
00:26:43,867 --> 00:26:45,808
(Jung-yeon is pretty.)

259
00:26:56,239 --> 00:26:57,878
Back then, you were young.

260
00:26:59,284 --> 00:27:01,386
You were perfect as an experiment subject.

261
00:27:05,469 --> 00:27:07,003
Was that really all it was?

262
00:27:09,513 --> 00:27:10,863
And...

263
00:27:14,187 --> 00:27:15,480
Just...

264
00:27:17,552 --> 00:27:19,402
a cute student.

265
00:27:49,487 --> 00:27:54,815
(ECG Pattern: Abnormal conduction detected)
(Status: Emotional response baseline (Exceeded))

266
00:28:08,026 --> 00:28:09,324
Teacher.

267
00:28:13,274 --> 00:28:15,136
Can't you just live at our place?

268
00:28:18,655 --> 00:28:19,902
I really…

269
00:28:20,896 --> 00:28:22,964
I think I'd be fine as long as I have you.

270
00:29:00,105 --> 00:29:03,400
Hey, what's going on between you two?

271
00:29:05,788 --> 00:29:07,807
You're seriously suffocating me.

272
00:29:09,549 --> 00:29:11,369
I'll go to the restroom.

273
00:29:30,408 --> 00:29:33,057
Hey, did you do something to Jung-yeon?

274
00:29:35,416 --> 00:29:36,549
No?

275
00:29:38,224 --> 00:29:39,268
Really?

276
00:29:41,878 --> 00:29:45,423
But hey, Jung-yeon's experiment results—

277
00:29:45,448 --> 00:29:47,117
don't you think they're off?

278
00:29:47,142 --> 00:29:49,158
How do you even get a 99?

279
00:29:50,814 --> 00:29:52,149
That makes no sense.

280
00:29:52,174 --> 00:29:53,104
Look.

281
00:29:54,485 --> 00:29:56,541
I'm telling you,
this is my first time seeing this.

282
00:30:03,783 --> 00:30:05,065
I'll head out first.

283
00:30:05,336 --> 00:30:06,463
I'm leaving.

284
00:30:06,846 --> 00:30:09,432
Text me. Text me.

285
00:30:10,078 --> 00:30:13,498
(Myung-jin: Looking at the results, it's 100%—
he's got someone he likes right now.)

286
00:30:13,523 --> 00:30:14,932
(Myung-jin: Ask who it is.)

287
00:30:25,435 --> 00:30:28,455
Please call that person "Teacher".

288
00:30:34,128 --> 00:30:37,854
That experiment you said
you saw seven years ago—

289
00:30:45,267 --> 00:30:47,877
you're right. I used you.

290
00:30:50,895 --> 00:30:53,479
A rich kid hanging out with bad friends—

291
00:30:54,269 --> 00:30:55,588
it's a cliché.

292
00:31:00,232 --> 00:31:01,369
So what?

293
00:31:04,328 --> 00:31:06,748
Because of that, I got my act together.

294
00:31:07,354 --> 00:31:10,149
Sure, I repeated a year, but—

295
00:31:10,174 --> 00:31:12,768
I got into a good university.
That means it worked, right?

296
00:31:20,177 --> 00:31:22,689
For you, and for me.

297
00:31:24,144 --> 00:31:25,502
Jung-yeon…

298
00:31:29,762 --> 00:31:31,768
It's just that I feel guilty.

299
00:31:44,019 --> 00:31:45,353
So—

300
00:31:46,897 --> 00:31:48,950
that's why I came back, all grown up.

301
00:32:16,768 --> 00:32:18,130
Put that on.

302
00:32:19,853 --> 00:32:21,669
Let's run the final experiment.

303
00:32:31,532 --> 00:32:35,782
Case-Delphi.
We will proceed with the next question.

304
00:32:37,611 --> 00:32:39,282
About the other person—

305
00:32:40,259 --> 00:32:43,000
tell me what you've already come to like.

306
00:32:46,464 --> 00:32:48,466
At first,

307
00:32:48,466 --> 00:32:51,177
I liked him because he was handsome.

308
00:32:51,177 --> 00:32:53,721
And because he was kind.

309
00:32:56,391 --> 00:32:59,315
I liked how cold he could be,
almost frighteningly so, when he was firm.

310
00:33:00,652 --> 00:33:03,321
I liked that he tried to keep boundaries.

311
00:33:08,496 --> 00:33:10,003
But the best part—

312
00:33:12,092 --> 00:33:16,523
was finding out he'd been watching over me
this whole time.

313
00:33:16,548 --> 00:33:19,085
I liked that more than I could bear.

314
00:33:34,345 --> 00:33:35,789
Is there—

315
00:33:38,516 --> 00:33:40,132
even as a joke—

316
00:33:42,020 --> 00:33:46,607
something you should never say?

317
00:33:47,934 --> 00:33:49,590
Actually, it was all a lie.

318
00:33:51,154 --> 00:33:52,879
I never liked you.

319
00:33:54,965 --> 00:33:56,527
If tonight—

320
00:33:58,628 --> 00:34:03,113
you were to die without contacting anyone—

321
00:34:06,517 --> 00:34:08,582
of all the things you didn't get to say,

322
00:34:09,687 --> 00:34:12,379
what would you regret the most?

323
00:34:16,765 --> 00:34:17,975
And—

324
00:34:19,997 --> 00:34:24,527
who would you want to say it to?

325
00:34:26,680 --> 00:34:28,059
I like you.

326
00:34:28,542 --> 00:34:29,684
Hyung.

327
00:34:42,003 --> 00:34:43,832
This is the final question.

328
00:34:49,378 --> 00:34:51,762
Open up about your condition,

329
00:34:52,590 --> 00:34:54,738
and ask the other person for advice.

330
00:34:57,495 --> 00:34:58,871
Before—

331
00:35:00,715 --> 00:35:03,152
when I found that experiment notebook—

332
00:35:04,725 --> 00:35:07,902
I was angry, thinking you had deceived me.

333
00:35:15,177 --> 00:35:16,220
But—

334
00:35:21,728 --> 00:35:25,107
when I thought about how you'd been
watching me all this time,

335
00:35:29,252 --> 00:35:30,832
I liked that, too.

336
00:35:38,784 --> 00:35:40,449
I'm kind of strange, right?

337
00:35:41,759 --> 00:35:43,324
I still am.

338
00:35:44,938 --> 00:35:47,121
I don't mind if I'm just a test subject.

339
00:35:48,664 --> 00:35:50,520
I don't mind if you use me.

340
00:35:53,859 --> 00:35:57,660
I just want you to like me.

341
00:36:00,006 --> 00:36:01,543
I really—

342
00:36:03,176 --> 00:36:04,504
I like you so, so much.

343
00:36:24,223 --> 00:36:25,324
<i>Finally</i>

344
00:36:28,284 --> 00:36:29,949
<i>the experiment is over.</i>

345
00:36:37,476 --> 00:36:40,354
<i>Hey, but that experiment
you're doing with Jung-yeon—</i>

346
00:36:40,379 --> 00:36:42,234
<i>are you even reporting it to the company?</i>

347
00:36:42,598 --> 00:36:44,726
<i>That's the experiment
we did back in undergrad.</i>

348
00:36:45,445 --> 00:36:49,348
(How do you even get a 99 for Jeong-yeon's results?
That makes no sense.)

349
00:36:49,373 --> 00:36:50,708
(Are you seeing someone right now?)

350
00:36:50,708 --> 00:36:53,046
<i>As you exchange questions back and forth,</i>

351
00:36:53,544 --> 00:36:55,046
(It was my most precious memory.)

352
00:36:55,046 --> 00:36:57,788
<i>at some point, you end up confessing
even your real feelings,</i>

353
00:36:58,797 --> 00:37:01,226
<i>and by the time
you get to the last question—</i>

354
00:37:01,251 --> 00:37:02,753
(Do you still like me?)

355
00:37:02,778 --> 00:37:04,843
<i>you fall in love with each other.</i>

356
00:37:06,119 --> 00:37:09,330
<i>Arthur Aron's 36 Questions Experiment.</i>

357
00:37:09,355 --> 00:37:11,359
<i>That's it, right?</i>

358
00:37:11,694 --> 00:37:14,101
Yes, Professor. How have you been?

359
00:37:14,370 --> 00:37:16,015
I'm calling because—

360
00:37:16,040 --> 00:37:17,543
about that assistant researcher

361
00:37:17,568 --> 00:37:19,562
I mentioned last time—

362
00:37:19,780 --> 00:37:24,382
I found someone who wrote their thesis
on the self-control of at-risk youth.

363
00:37:25,618 --> 00:37:27,202
What do you think about that person?

364
00:37:28,499 --> 00:37:29,624
Yes.

365
00:37:30,221 --> 00:37:31,554
Thank you.

366
00:38:01,776 --> 00:38:03,447
(Jung-yeon… you…)

367
00:38:07,097 --> 00:38:09,541
(you've become perfectly mine.)

368
00:38:57,418 --> 00:39:00,871
Name three things you have in common
with the other person.

369
00:39:01,979 --> 00:39:03,564
Hmm…

370
00:39:03,589 --> 00:39:05,082
Good at studying?

371
00:39:06,103 --> 00:39:07,771
Only think about one person,

372
00:39:09,044 --> 00:39:10,652
and… can't help but caring about him?

373
00:39:11,732 --> 00:39:14,207
What is your most precious memory?

374
00:39:16,359 --> 00:39:18,652
The day I first met him.

375
00:39:19,444 --> 00:39:23,615
Back then, he was just a sweet kid
who looked like he needed help.

376
00:39:27,471 --> 00:39:31,394
My experiment was meant to help
someone like that.

377
00:39:38,774 --> 00:39:41,603
But when I saw him come back all grown up—

378
00:39:43,484 --> 00:39:45,744
the results of the experiment
no longer mattered.

379
00:39:47,051 --> 00:39:49,884
What does a “perfect” day look like to you?

380
00:39:52,344 --> 00:39:53,931
The day—

381
00:39:55,229 --> 00:39:57,595
The day Jung-yeon is entirely in my arms.

382
00:40:09,263 --> 00:40:10,861
(I…)

383
00:40:11,351 --> 00:40:14,494
(I knew everything, teacher.)

384
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:22,901
Me too.

385
00:40:24,912 --> 00:40:27,189
I like you too, Jung-yeon.

386
00:40:30,466 --> 00:40:31,717
Me too, hyung.
